<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>There are cases where Zend_Service_Twitter can be used without authentication, but the constructor requires $username and $password to always be passed. For example, checking if a given username exists or not:</p>

<p>$tw = new Zend_Service_Twitter(null);
$exists = $tw-&gt;user-&gt;show($who)-&gt;id() !== null;</p>

<p>Since the first parameter is required, one can't simply do this:</p>

<p>$tw = new Zend_Service_Twitter();</p>

<p>I'd like to propose that both constructor parameters should be optional, in order to more cleanly support these anonymous uses.</p>

